OL,3,CRamsay MacDonald: The first Labour
OL,4,CPrime Minister who still divides
OL,5,Copinion
OL,7,FMacDonald, then MP for Seaham,
OL,8,Freturned as Prime Minister in 1929. He
OL,9,Fagain led a minority Labour government
OL,10,Funtil 1931, where amid a global
OL,11,Ffinancial crisis, he agreed to the
OL,12,FKing's request to lead a national
OL,13,Fgovernment - a coalition dominated by
OL,14,FConservatives.
OL,16,FHe was expelled from the Labour Party
OL,17,Fas a result and has still not been
OL,18,Fforgiven for his actions.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
