OL,3,CRamsay MacDonald: The first Labour
OL,4,CPrime Minister who still divides
OL,5,Copinion
OL,7,F"Certainly in the mining communities
OL,8,Fthat bore the brunt of the cuts in
OL,9,Fwages and the terrible reductions in
OL,10,Fconditions, I think he is considered
OL,11,Fto be a class traitor," said Labour MP
OL,12,Ffor Easington Grahame Morris. "But I
OL,13,Fthink history's been a bit kinder in
OL,14,Fretrospect."
OL,16,FMacDonald stood down as Prime Minister
OL,17,Fin 1935, again to be replaced by
OL,18,FBaldwin. He lost his Seaham seat later
OL,19,Fto Labour candidate Manny Shinwell.
